Nowa Makula, 32, the man accused of hacking an Elliotdale family of six to death last week, will make a formal bail application on December 7. Makula, was the boyfriend of the mother and father of three of the children who were hacked to death with an axe, including a six-month-old baby. The horrific scene was discovered by the mother's 16-year-old son. The killings have made headlines in South Africa and internationally and came as the country started it's 16 Days of Activism against Gender-based Violence campaign. He made his first court appearance in the Elliotdale magistrate's court on Monday before the matter was postponed for the bail application.